snippet: Lieuwe Westra of the Netherlands attacked late in the final climb of the day to win the fifth stage of the Paris-Nice race.
abstract: Dutch cyclist Lieuwe Westra wins fifth stage of the Paris-Nice race; Bradley Wiggins extends his overall lead; other cycling news noted.
lead_paragraph: Lieuwe Westra of the Netherlands attacked late in the final climb of the day to win the fifth stage of the Paris-Nice race.
